      <h1 class='work_name'>Profile</h1>

      <p>
        <strong>BINOCLE</strong> is the office led by Italian architect Lorenzo Bini that deals with
        the transformation of existing spaces, from temporary structures to permanent buildings and gardens.
      </p>

      <p>
        Born in 1971 and educated in Milan and Oslo, Lorenzo graduated in 1998 from Politecnico di
        Milano and worked in Milan and Rotterdam until 2003 when he started his own practice in
        Milano.
      </p>

      <p>
        Alongside the professional activity, Lorenzo has taught at the Politecnico di Milano, at the
        Design Academy Eindhoven and at NABA, Nuova Accademia di Belle Arti in Milan.
      </p>

      <p>
        In 2021 he became a member of the Council of the Order of Architects, Landscape Planners and
        Conservators of the Province of Milan with responsibility for cultural activities.
